D. P. PAUL & CO., Appellee, v. Maurice CAMPBELL, Federal Prohibition Administrator, et al., Appellants. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. July 8, 1929. No. 350. See, also, 24 F.(2d) 738. Charles H. Tuttle, U. S. Atty., of New York City (U. S. Grant, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellants. Charles Diekerman Williams, of New York City, for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Deeree affirmed, on the authority of Lion Laboratories v. Campbell (C. C. A.) 34 F.(2d) 642, handed down herewith.
